The paper deals with multi-winner elections and axioms related to representation, which are topics in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also proposes a relaxation of an axiom and discusses its computational complexity, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses mathematical tools and analysis to prove results, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.SI).
